quran[19]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,172,"[That] indeed, they would be those given victory"
  37,173,"And [that] indeed, Our soldiers [i.e., the believers] will be those who overcome.{1}",footnotes:1:[If not in this world, then definitely in the Hereafter.]
  37,174,"So, [O Muḥammad], leave them for a time."
  43,61,"And indeed, he [i.e., Jesus] will be [a sign for] knowledge of the Hour, so be not in doubt of it, and follow Me.{1} This is a straight path.",footnotes:1:[i.e., follow the guidance and instruction of Allāh.]
  43,62,"And never let Satan avert you. Indeed, he is to you a clear enemy."
  43,63,"And when Jesus brought clear proofs, he said, "
  44,46,"Like the boiling of scalding water."
  44,47,"[It will be commanded], "
  44,48,"Then pour over his head from the torment of scalding water."
  45,37,"And to Him belongs [all] grandeur within the heavens and the earth, and He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise."
  46,25,"Destroying everything by command of its Lord. And they became so that nothing was seen [of them] except their dwellings. Thus do We recompense the criminal people."
  46,26,"And We had certainly established them in such as We have not established you, and We made for them hearing and vision and hearts [i.e., intellect]. But their hearing and vision and hearts availed them not from anything [of the punishment] when they were [continually] rejecting the signs of Allāh; and they were enveloped by what they used to ridicule."
  46,27,"And We have already destroyed what surrounds you of [those] cities, and We have diversified the signs [or verses] that perhaps they might return [from disbelief]."
  47,16,"And among them, [O Muḥammad], are those who listen to you, until when they depart from you, they say to those who were given knowledge,{1} ",footnotes:1:[From among the Prophet's companions.]
  47,17,"And those who are guided - He increases them in guidance and gives them their righteousness.{1}",footnotes:1:[Taqwā, meaning piety, consciousness and fear of Allāh, and care to avoid His displeasure.]
  47,18,"Then do they await except that the Hour should come upon them unexpectedly? But already there have come [some of] its indications. Then how [i.e., what good] to them, when it has come, will be their remembrance?"
  48,7,"And to Allāh belong the soldiers of the heavens and the earth. And ever is Allāh Exalted in Might and Wise."
  48,8,"Indeed, We have sent you as a witness and a bringer of good tidings and a warner"
  48,9,"That you [people] may believe in Allāh and His Messenger and honor him and respect him [i.e., the Prophet (ﷺ)] and exalt Him [i.e., Allāh] morning and afternoon."